item.dc:creator: crdunsto_main
item.content:encoded:
Profile

I am a Web and Graphic Designer forging powerful, creative identity systems.

I love Design, and have learned Front-End Development along the way. User Interfaces, Software Engineering and the Adobe Suite - everything from Color Theory to fire type combos to code to is in my wheelhouse.

Goals

To self-actualize as a Designer/Developer as part of a competitive and diverse agency is my aim. The winds are shifting us to rounded corners, js frameworks, and etc... I want to find the core of what makes the digital experience gratifying, what gives it its ethos, and then project that in the most beautiful, ethical way imaginable.

item.title: Policy Research Forum

wp:postmeta.wp:meta_value:
About

Research project. Presentation on state and national trends in mental health policy, and effect on those suffering from SMI. Research: NAMI and Treatment Advocacy Center studies, and the Mental Health Reform Act of 2015/16.

Findings

Recent cuts in state funding of mental health facilities in states like Illinois was made palatable by most of these patients already being in jail. Compound this with already anemic access to basic services and opt-outs against expanding Medicaid for those meeting 138% of the federal poverty line (less than $14,000) by legislatures. These conditions - not without a lack of Intervention Training for law enforcement and weak public commitment laws - leave the poor untreated, underserved, and more likely to be criminalized.

item.title: Hendricks Chapel

wp:postmeta.wp:meta_value:
Hendricks Chapel

The Chapel is Syracuse University's cultural heart and hosts nine interfaith Chaplaincies, a student-run coffee shop, and the Office of Engagement, which supports students and the community through events and services.

Fall '18 — Summer '19

Much of the work was on a new web app. The latest web technologies (Wordpress Native API, Angular JS) were employed and everything from Information Architecture to User Personas/Flows were developed and implemented via a component-based, responsive user interface.

Scope

I worked on event collaterals such as social media images, posters, and other signage. I helped draft and design booklets and other promotional information highlighting ways in which Dean Konkl and the Chapel help people in and around the community.
